28. Juvenal employs the imperatives aspice, respice, and accipe as forms ol transition; as

14. 27 5 aspice portus et plenum magnis trabibus mare; 3. 268 respice nunc alia ac diversa pericula noctis; 7. 36 accipe nuncartes. Cf. also aspiceres 15. 56, and operaepretium est 14. 281.

The conjunction itaque is nowhere found in Juvenal.

29. An accusative of a proper name is used with vivere to denote an attribute of the substantive idea contained in the verb; as

2. 3 qui Curios simulant et Bacchanalia mount, ie. live a Bacchanalian liie; 12.128 vivat Pacuvius, quaeso, vel Nestora totum, ie. live a lite quite as long as Nestor's.

30. With similis, dissimilis (except 10.192 dissimilemque sui) and diversus the dative only is used; as

11. 194 similisque triumphe praetor sedet; 3. 18 speluncas dissimiles veris; 10. 3 illis multum diversa.

31. With aptus, maturus, and utilis Juvenal employs the dative ol the gerundive; as

15. 14 5 exercendis pariendisque arts'bus apti; &169 maturus bello Armeniae Syn'aeque tuendis amnibus ; 14. 72 utilis et bellorum et pacis rebus agendis.
